column139: Before diving into complex ensemble models, we built a robust preprocessing pipeline:\n
column141: - **One-Hot Encoding** was used to convert categorical features into numerical format, enabling model compatibility.\n
column142: - **Missing values** were handled using the **median imputation strategy**, ensuring no data leakage.\n
column143: - **Standardization** was applied to normalize features, which is essential for models like Logistic Regression.\n
column144: - Finally, we trained a simple **Logistic Regression** model as a baseline to benchmark our modeling efforts.\n
